-- Shenzhen Energy First-Half Profit Declines 16% on Increased Cost for Fuel
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-21T10:10:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-21/shenzhen-energy-first-half-profit-declines-16-on-increased-cost-for-fuel.html

          
          
             Shenzhen Energy Group Co.’s first-
half net income fell 16 percent to 876 million yuan due to the
increased cost of fuel the company bought for generating
electricity, according to a statement to Shenzhen’s stock
exchange.  
 First-half sales rose 44.5 percent to 6.1 billion yuan,
according to the statement.  
